node.text:
Swipe to bake ✨ (ad) there’s a new recipe on the blog today for this blueberry balsamic crostata! (I’m calling it a crostata as it’s in the style of one but it’s also a tart / pie hybrid?) regardless of what you call it it’s SO good. I developed this months ago and have been so excited to share! There’s a flaky crust and a balsamic berry filling made with my fave @filippoberio_us balsamic vinegar. The filling works perfectly with both fresh and frozen fruit if berries aren’t in season where you are! And pie crust + tart pan = most epic filling to crust ratio! This one is so, so good, I hope you enjoy 💕 recipe is linked in my bio! #filippoberio #sponsored 
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
These twisty cinnamon buns are on the blog today! They look super fancy but the process is really easy - it’s just a rolled up braid. These are made with my small batch no mixer brioche, which is my current fave (it’s just a half batch of my regular dough). These wee buns are so soft, and just so, so good. Link is in my bio 💕
.
.

.
.

node.text: Just in case you were wondering… this method for lining a 9x13 works perfectly on tiny sheet pans using tiny parchment paper. It’s my fave way to line a pan. Cut slits about in line with the sides and about as deep as the pan, then push down and arrange the strips. I grease my pan first to make it easy, you don’t have to if you don’t want to. Tiny sheet cakes for the win. 💕😍 #lifehacks #oddlysatisfying #bakingtips

node.text:
Pizza pretzels are on the blog today! I scaled back my recipe and tweaked the dough formula a wee bit so this makes 6 super chewy, cheesy pizza pretzels. Leave the pepperoni off if you want, add in other stuff, you do you. All the details including info about TINY PEPPERONI are on the blog post, link in my bio!

.

node.text:
You truly can’t go wrong with a good Funfetti. This one in particular is 🔥. It’s made in a six inch pan but I’ve got a handy wee calculator adventure dad made me which you can plug the pan size in and it tells you what to scale the recipe by. It’s linked just above the recipe card in every recipe on my site. There’s also one for calculating bread hydration, and a wee handy calculator that converts grams to cups, just for marilyn 😂😅 recipe link for the cake is in my bio!
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
I don’t really have a content calendar (I need to but winging it works ok too), but I love a good bandwagon jump and I saw some whispers of another useless internet holiday, this time about s’mores, so here’s a pic I post often but these no bake small batch s’mores bars are just 🔥. I adapted them from a s’mores tart on my site from yonks ago which is good too but I really just love a loaf pan situation. Recipe link is in my bio 💕 
.

node.text:
Had my first custard square since being back in Nz (it was a denheath - IYKYK 😍) and just wanted to remind you I have a banger of a custard square recipe on my website too - theres steps for making your own puff or you can use store bought too and it will be 🔥 either way. Recipe link is in my bio ❤️ (yes I know Australians incorrectly call it vanilla slice but this is a Nz recipe so we use the correct name 😂😏)

node.text:
Refreshed my rhubarb shortcake recipe for you and it now has two gravel smoothing elements in it 😂 this is what we call shortcake in Nz - one dough that forms the base and topping. It’s super good with rhubarb but also amazing with stone fruit (plum is 🙌🏻), cranberries or berries. The recipe is linked in my bio! It originally had two pieces of pastry that got rolled out but I sent the recipe to @ohyeahnahbro and she worked some pastry magic on it and made it way easier so I had to also do that 😂💕 enjoy! ❤️
.
